name: Seasons
description:
You are given a name of a month. Output the season of the year to which it
belongs (based on Northern hemisphere). Input The input consists of a single
string containing the name of one of the twelve months (January, February,
March, April, May, June, July, August, September, October, November or
December). The string is capitalized as given here. Output Output a single
string — the season of the year to which the given month belongs (winter,
spring, summer or autumn). The name of the season should be in lowercase.
Examples Input April Output spring Input November Output autumn Note Assume
that winter is December through February, spring is March through May, summer
is June through August and autumn is September through November.
